Pre-Game Insights: Australia looks set to welcome back Travis Head from injury while the Netherlands need some runs from their top-order

For all the links between to the two nations as far as players and coaches are concerned, Australia and Netherlands have only met twice in ODI cricket. Both matches were at World Cups, in 2003 and 2007, and Australia were ruthless, claiming big wins while tinkering with their line-up.
Others: The three games in Delhi thus far in this World Cup have produced two very different results, although the common thread is that the side batting first has won easily.
